      <h2 id="introduction">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        The Music Search Website is a web application that allows users to
        search for songs and artists and get music preview links from Spotify
        and Apple Music. Users can search for their favorite songs and discover
        new music through this website.
      </p>

      <h2 id="features">2. Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Search for songs and artists.</li>
        <li>Get preview links for songs on Spotify and Apple Music.</li>
        <li>Responsive design for mobile and desktop devices.</li>
        <li>Attractive user interface.</li>
        <li>Error handling for invalid searches.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="getting-started">3. Getting Started</h2>
      <h3 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h3>
      <p>To run this project locally, you will need the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager) installed on your machine.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Clone the repository:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre><code style="color: black;">git clone https://github.com/your-username/music-search-website.git</code></pre>
      <ol start="2">
        <li>Navigate to the project directory:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre><code style="color: black;">cd music-search-website</code></pre>
      <ol start="3">
        <li>Install the required dependencies:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre><code style="color: black;">npm install</code></pre>
      <ol start="4">
        <li>Start the development server:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre><code style="color: black;">npm start</code></pre>

      <h2 id="project-structure">4. Project Structure</h2>
      <pre><code style="color: black;">
music-search-website/
  ├
  ├── src/
  │   ├── server.js
