        </li>
        <li><code>styles/</code>: Contains custom styles for the website.</li>
        <li><code>data/</code>: Contains the JSON file with song data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="technologies-used">5. Technologies Used</h2>
      <p>The Music Search Website is built using the following technologies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Front-end:
          <ul>
            <li>HTML</li>
            <li>CSS</li>
            <li>JavaScript (Vanilla JS)</li>
            <li>EJS (Embedded JavaScript) for templating</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Back-end:
          <ul>
            <li>Node.js</li>
            <li>Express.js for handling server requests</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="usage">6. Usage</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the website using your preferred web browser.</li>
        <li>
          Enter the name of a song or artist in the search bar and click the
          "Search" button.
        </li>
        <li>
          The website will display a list of search results containing song
          details, including the song name, artist name, album name, and preview
          links for Spotify and Apple Music.
        </li>
        <li>
          If no results are found, an appropriate message will be displayed.
        </li>
        <li>
          You can listen to a preview of the song by using the audio player
          embedded in the search results.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 id="responsive-design">7. Responsive Design</h2>
